name: places/ChIJ_UnySKwR2jERGjqg_X8yokk/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURMek5uNW5BRRAB
text: {'text': 'Love this Catholic Church with nice architecture. It gives a sense of peace and solitude. The compound is big and has a lot of carpark and buildings, first time visitors might need a little navigation. The interior and exterior of the church are simply beautiful and comfortable. There is a multi-purpose space within walkable distance from church that can be used as cafeteria for event and the size is decent to fit plenty of people.\n\n(Photos copyright by @KAI_Picture )', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJ_UnySKwR2jERGjqg_X8yokk/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURadlB6aGl3RRAB
text:
{'text': "A place of refuge, peace, solace and solitude for many. Also, one of the biggest Catholic Churches in Singapore.

Equipped with a host of features for quiet prayer and contemplation, such as the Rosary Garden, Grotto of Our Lady, and the life-sized Stations of the Cross. There are 6 designated parking spaces, and even a dedicated area for motorcycles.

There are classrooms, halls, and AVA rooms available for booking, should you need them for appropriate events.

There is a canteen run by various church ministries on Sundays, and one can expect sumptuous local delights for breakfast. On other days, there is a cafe (Benedito) located at CTIS for a quiet coffee/tea moment.

The church is child and elderly friendly, with a large cry room for parents, and wheelchair accessible zones for those who have limited mobility.

Hospitality is top-notch, as the Wardens are approachable, and ready to attend to your needs.

Non-catholics are welcome, and are never turned away. Regardless if they're just visiting, or there to learn about the faith.

If you ever find yourself lost, do pay them a visit. You might find something more than just directions to where you might be headed to.", 'languageCode': 'en'}
